name: Microbiology Chapter 24 Homework
description: Homework questions for Chapter 24, focusing on GERD.
subject: Microbiology

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: GERD is also known as acid reflux.
questions.explanation: Gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD) is the clinical name for acid reflux.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: GERD occurs when the food in the small intestine returns back to the esophagus.
questions.explanation: GERD occurs when stomach contents, not contents from the small intestine, flow back into the esophagus.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: GERD occurs when the LES is strong.
questions.explanation: GERD is often caused by a weak or improperly functioning lower esophageal sphincter (LES).

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The condition where part of the stomach pushes up through the diaphragm, as shown in the associated image, is known as a hiatal hernia.
questions.explanation: A hiatal hernia, where part of the stomach protrudes through the diaphragm, is a common cause of GERD.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: A shorter dinner to bedtime is not a contributing factor to GERD.
questions.explanation: A short interval between dinner and bedtime is a contributing factor to GERD as it does not allow the stomach to empty before lying down.
